<P>
19 SEIZED IN CLINIC PROTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Singing "Jesus Loves the Little Children," 19 demonstrators were arrested after 
blocking access to a private abortion clinic in Ventura. Organizers of the 
demonstration -- the first such protest in Ventura County -- said its timing 
was incidental to the U.S. Supreme Court decision this week allowing states to 
bar publicly funded abortions. "Our purpose is to lay our bodies down to rescue 
the babies scheduled to be murdered today," said Jill Craft, a spokeswoman for 
Operation Rescue. The demonstrators sat in the doorway and along the corridor 
outside Family Planning Associates Medical Group as employees of the private 
clinic were arriving for work. With the clinic effectively shut, patients and 
staff members milled around in the parking lot. Also held back were 10 clinic 
security guards, who were warned by police not to attempt to open the doors or 
escort patients inside for fear they might inflame the crowd. "This is 
Ventura," said Lt. Pat Rooney, "and we're going to keep the peace." 
