<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CHATSWORTH MAN GETS 8 YEARS IN FATAL SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A27-year old Chatsworth man was sentenced to eight years in prison Thursday for 
fatally shooting a man during an argument. 
</P>
<P>
Zeferino Rosales Leon pleaded guilty in April to first-degree manslaughter in 
the death of Ignacio Gomez, 26. Leon originally was charged with murder, but 
that charge was dismissed when he agreed to plead to the lesser crime. 
</P>
<P>
Gomez died of medical complications from the bullet wound on May 18, 1988 -- 
more than six weeks after the shooting took place. 
</P>
<P>
During the sentencing, Public Defender Jerry M. Schultz pleaded with San 
Fernando Superior Court Judge Meredith Taylor not to give Leon the maximum 
13-year sentence, arguing that Gomez's death was caused as much by medical 
negligence as by Leon's actions. 
</P>
<P>
According to court documents, Gomez was released from Northridge Hospital 
Medical Center less than a week after the shooting. A month later, he returned 
to the hospital, complaining of discomfort and was referred to the Los Angeles 
County-USC Medical Center, where he died. 
</P>
</TEXT>
