<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BODY OF FISHERMAN, 67, FOUND IN AQUEDUCT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of a Los Angeles man who fell into the California Aqueduct near Gorman 
on Tuesday was found 20 miles downstream by fishermen Thursday morning, the Los 
Angeles County Sheriff's Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
Willie Clark, 67, had been missing since 12:30 a.m. Tuesday when a companion 
saw him fall into the aqueduct while the two were fishing, Deputy Detta Roberts 
said. Sheriff's rescue crews were unable to find the man in the rapidly moving 
water and abandoned their search Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Fishermen discovered the body floating in the aqueduct near 80th Street West, 
near Palmdale. 
</P>
