<TEXT>
<P>
About 25 aliens, most of them Mexicans, were arrested by 90 American 
immigration agents during a two-hour investigation of the barn area at 
Hollywood Park. The aliens taken into custody were charged with having 
counterfeit immigration documents. 
</P>
<P>
"I find it encouraging that we found so few," said Hal Ezell, regional 
commissioner of the United States Immigration and Naturalization Service. "In 
recent years, we've found hundreds of illegals at California tracks. I think 
this shows that our employer-sanction program is working." 
</P>
