<P>
THE BIGGEST ACCOUNTING FIRMS 
</P>
<P>
Ranking is based on the firms' fiscal 1988 revenue from U.S. operations, as 
compiled by Bowman's Accounting Report of Atlanta. The list assumes completion 
of the merger announced in May of Ernst &amp; Whinney with Arthur Young &amp; 
Co., formerly third and sixth, respectively. On Thursday, Deloitte Haskins 
&amp; Sells and Touche Ross announced an agreement in principle to merge. 
Separately, Arthur Andersen and Price Waterhouse disclosed that they have begun 
formal merger talks. 
</P>
