<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMI's Board Meets: American Medical International's board met to consider 
acquisition bids for the company. A group led by the New York buyout firm 
Clayton &amp; Dubilier renewed its offer to acquire the Beverly Hills-based 
hospital management firm by offering $24 per share, or $1.7 billion, according 
to a document filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The group set 
a June 15 deadline when it made the offer June 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
