<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Merger Activity Drops: Despite several large corporate acquisitions proposed in 
the first half of 1989, merger activity is lagging behind the pace set last 
year, according to a report by Securities Data Co. An analysis by Securities 
Data of deals worth $10 million or more showed that there was $164.9 billion in 
activity in the first half of 1989, representing 695 announced deals, compared 
to $209.5 billion in 784 deals in the comparable period last year. The report 
also showed that only 24 deals worth $1 billion or more were reported in the 
period, compared to 52 a year earlier. 
</P>
