<P>
MOBSTER GENE GOTTI GETS 50 YEARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gene Gotti, brother of Gambino mob boss John Gotti, was sentenced today to 50 
years in prison for running a multimillion-dollar drug ring. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. District Judge John R. Bartels ignored defense lawyers' appeals for mercy 
in handing down the maximum sentence. "I have my obligations," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Co-defendant John Carneglia was also given 50 years and both were fined $75,000 
each. Gotti, 42, and Carneglia, 44, were found guilty May 23 of being at the 
center of a major heroin trafficking ring. Authorities describe Gotti as a capo 
or captain in the Gambino crime family and Carneglia as a soldier in the 
organization. 
</P>
