<P>
NAMES IN THE NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
HIROHITO ESTATE PUT AT $13.36 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japan's Emperor Hirohito, who died last month at 87, left assets worth $13.36 
million, according to the first public accounting of imperial family private 
property, the Imperial Household Agency said today. 
</P>
<P>
Emperor Akihito and Empress dowager Nagako equally divided the estate except 
for about 3,000 works of art that were donated to the state. 
</P>
<P>
The agency said the decision was based on consultation among Hirohito's 11 
closest relatives, indicating that nine had given up any claim on the estate. 
</P>
<P>
The royal family's real estate, including about 5,436 acres of land, are exempt 
from taxation because they are considered state land under the postwar 
constitution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
