<P>
LOS ALAMITOS MAN HELD IN SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 53-year-old Los Alamitos man was arrested in connection with the shooting 
death of his son-in-law, who was found dead on his front lawn in Orange, police 
said today. 
</P>
<P>
James Rovida Jr., a self-employed truck driver, was being held in Orange County 
Jail today on suspicion of murder, Orange Police Detective Dave Hill said. 
</P>
<P>
The body of Rovida's son-in-law, Robert Brock, was found about 3 a.m. Thursday 
on the front lawn of a Quincy Avenue home that Brock shared with his sister, 
Hill said. Neighbors had heard gunshots and notified police, Hill said. 
</P>
<P>
Hill said Brock had two gunshot wounds, possibly from a medium-caliber pistol. 
Police arrested Rovida hours later, partly on information from neighbors and 
from Brock's sister about a pickup truck whose driver fled the scene just after 
the shooting, Hill said. 
</P>
