<HEADLINE>
<P>
FUROR OVER FLAG BURNING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Surely the Founding Fathers never had in mind the burning of the American flag 
when they penned the First Amendment to the Constitution! Since when does an 
act of the will (burning the flag) equal the spoken word (freedom of speech)? 
</P>
<P>
I deplore the recent Supreme Court decision which allows anyone the freedom to 
desecrate the American flag when he is disgruntled, while standing on its ashes 
with raised fist against America. Bravo, President Bush; plaudits to you for 
standing up for this American symbol. Patriotism has never gone out of style, 
nor should it! 
</P>
<P>
LYNNE TRUJILLO 
</P>
<P>
Irvine 
</P>
